  "id": "019d286a-f2d8-78b2-92cd-56a5f0f34c0e",
  "content": "    let sources: Vec<Value> = response.context.sources.iter().map(|r| {\n        serde_json::json!({\n            \"content\": r.entry.content,\n            \"score\": r.score,\n            \"source_file\": r.entry.metadata.source_file,\n        })\n    }).collect();\n\n    Ok(json!({\n        \"content\": [{\n            \"type\": \"text\",\n            \"text\": serde_json::to_string_pretty(&json!({\n                \"answer\": response.answer,\n                \"sources\": sources,\n                \"trace\": response.trace,\n            })).unwrap()\n        }]\n    }))\n}\n```\n\n**Step 4: Fix corvia_search to route through RAG when available**\n\nUpdate `tool_corvia_search` to use the RAG pipeline when available (same pattern as REST fix in Task 9).\n\n**Step 5: Update test_state to include rag: None**\n\nUpdate the test helper:\n\n```rust\n    async fn test_state(dir: &std::path::Path) -> Arc<AppState> {\n        let store = Arc::new(LiteStore::open(dir, 3).unwrap()) as Arc<dyn QueryableStore>;\n        let engine = Arc::new(MockEngine) as Arc<dyn InferenceEngine>;\n        store.init_schema().await.unwrap();\n        Arc::new(AppState { store, engine, coordinator: None, rag: None })\n    }\n```\n\n**Step 6: Verify compilation and tests pass**\n\nRun: `cargo test -p corvia-server -- --nocapture`\nExpected: all tests PASS, tools_list now shows 6 tools\n\n**Step 7: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add crates/corvia-server/src/mcp.rs\ngit commit -m \"feat(m3.2): MCP corvia_context + corvia_ask tools; fix corvia_search routing\"\n```\n\n---\n",
